p: A total of 44 compounds were identified, representing 84.59% for L1, 92.50% for L2, 91.83% for L3, and 87.20% for L4. Guaiol, atractylone, β-copaen-4-α-ol, cis-cadina-1,4-diene, β-copaen-4-α-ol and germacrene B were most abundant chemical compounds in L1. For L2, they were cis-cadina-1(6),4-diene, myrcene, atractylone, β-Copaen-4-α-ol and germacrene B. For L3, they were atractylone, myrcene, germacrene B, β-copaen-4-α-ol, α-pinene and β-pinene. Finally in L4, germacrene B, myrcene, cis-cadina-1(6),4-diene, α-selinene and cis-guaia-3,9-dien-11-ol were most abundant chemical compounds ( Table 1).
